grinding their asses off

04:00.073 --> 04:01.673
To get this place reopened?

04:01.742 --> 04:03.475
And by everyone else,
I mean me.

04:03.477 --> 04:05.410
The giver of life.

04:05.412 --> 04:07.713
- Tanning is work.
Look at her legs.

04:07.848 --> 04:10.114
- Yeah, don't you care about
optics? You want us to be

04:10.150 --> 04:12.383
The moonshine's own best
advertisement, don't you?

04:12.419 --> 04:15.087
- What I care about is you
boning that biker

04:15.089 --> 04:16.154
So we don't get boned.

04:16.156 --> 04:18.090
It's much more fun
than a bank loan.

04:18.092 --> 04:19.624
Think of the cash we could
be making.

04:19.660 --> 04:21.426
I mean, you might even
get your rebuild.

04:21.561 --> 04:24.562
- No, we are not getting
into bed... Business...

04:24.564 --> 04:27.699
With bikers. I'll find
another way.

04:27.735 --> 04:30.401
- Move!
(engine sputters and starts)

04:31.438 --> 04:34.172
Or I will shred you
into fertilizer!

04:34.241 --> 04:36.174
- Motherhood is really
softening her edges.

04:36.176 --> 04:40.078
- God, so cranky.
- Or annoying. Okay, okay.

04:40.213 --> 04:42.714
- We're polite.
- We're going, come on.

04:42.750 --> 04:45.150
- Buzzkill.
- I know, buzzkill!

04:45.152 --> 04:46.985
(engine roars)

04:46.987 --> 04:50.088
(motor revs,
water splashing)

04:51.659 --> 04:54.592
Man: Dude, last night
was crunk!

04:54.628 --> 04:57.562
- Yeah, you know it!
- All right! Later, bro!

04:57.564 --> 04:59.898
- Best of the republic
of good times!

05:00.033 --> 05:01.767
(engine roars away)

05:01.769 --> 05:05.203
Crystal: (giggles) ry!
Ry, look!

05:05.339 --> 05:08.673
The all you can flush grand
re-opening balloons came in.

05:08.676 --> 05:11.009
(squealing) with helium.
(giggles)

05:13.180 --> 05:15.814
Have you been drinking?
- No, I'm all good.

05:15.883 --> 05:19.084
- 'cause like, I would
understand, if you were.

05:19.153 --> 05:20.619
You know, but it's not
your fault

05:20.754 --> 05:23.088
That we lost the apartment.
- Literally was.

05:23.223 --> 05:25.990
I forgot to pay the rent.
- Yes, or, it was just the...

05:26.060 --> 05:29.427
The universe telling us
that it wasn't meant to be.

05:29.496 --> 05:32.698
Oh. Oh, crap.
Oh, crap, crap. Crap!

05:32.833 --> 05:34.432
- Or that.
- Crap!

05:34.501 --> 05:36.301
(exasperated exhales)

05:37.971 --> 05:39.838
(engine rumbles by)

05:39.840 --> 05:43.040
♪♪♪

05:43.077 --> 05:44.643
(cap rattles closed)
ugh.

05:46.880 --> 05:48.679
(package crinkles)

05:49.249 --> 05:51.082
(paper rustles)

05:51.085 --> 05:52.784
- Oxford?
What's that about?

05:52.853 --> 05:54.986
- Grad school interview.
Maybe.

05:54.988 --> 05:56.822
- England. So cool.

05:56.957 --> 05:58.724
Even the inbred royals
who reject women

05:58.859 --> 06:00.191
Who have their own minds
and opinions.

06:00.227 --> 06:01.960
- Best anthropology departments
in the world.

06:02.095 --> 06:03.862
- Man, if I had a free pass
outta here--

06:03.931 --> 06:06.731
- Not free. I have to get
a scholarship.

06:06.734 --> 06:09.634
I don't even know
if I wanna go, you know?

06:09.636 --> 06:11.869
The moonshine needs me.
I can't leave.

06:13.073 --> 06:15.874
Okay, fine, I'm making excuses.
- Uncle sammy--

06:15.876 --> 06:18.710
You can be the glue
or the glue gun.

06:18.779 --> 06:21.213
The stuff that sticks shit
together around here,

06:21.215 --> 06:23.714
Or the tool that controls
is own destiny.

06:25.018 --> 06:28.085
- She just called you a tool.
- No, she called me stuck.

06:28.122 --> 06:30.188
- We're all stuck.
- It's true.

06:30.190 --> 06:32.691
Can check out any time you
like, but no one ever leaves.

06:32.826 --> 06:35.226
- Okay, never quote don henley
in front of me. Ever.

06:35.295 --> 06:37.329
- Who? I just made that up.

06:37.464 --> 06:39.330
Sammy, you're 22.

06:39.400 --> 06:41.099
Not much time left.

06:42.636 --> 06:44.235
(package crinkles)

06:46.407 --> 06:48.006
- Addressed to the entire
family.

06:50.577 --> 06:52.410
- Not a bomb.

06:52.413 --> 06:54.212
(spray hisses,
cloth squeaks on window)

06:56.383 --> 06:57.983
(indistinct rattling)

06:59.086 --> 07:00.718
- (frustrated grunt)

07:00.720 --> 07:03.588
This old door needs replacing,
not repairing.

07:03.590 --> 07:06.291
You can't make a silk purse
out of a sow's ear.

07:06.426 --> 07:08.660
- Well, I happen to like
sow's ears.

07:08.729 --> 07:10.729
- Who replaced my wife
with an optimist?

07:10.731 --> 07:13.397
- (chuckles) a new grandchild
on the way.

07:13.434 --> 07:15.534
- Hmm.
- We have our home back.

07:15.669 --> 07:17.702
Things are finally
as they should be.

07:18.739 --> 07:20.538
Including my mood.

07:21.741 --> 07:23.541
- That's good enough for me.
- Mm-hmm.

07:23.610 --> 07:26.211
Sammy: Expecting a delivery?
(package crinkles)

07:26.346 --> 07:27.679
- Norway?

07:27.814 --> 07:29.747
- We owe money to someone
in norway?

07:29.783 --> 07:31.349
- Probably.

07:31.351 --> 07:32.884
(plastic crinkling)

07:38.425 --> 07:40.358
(suspenseful music)

07:40.360 --> 07:43.094
(gasps) christ on a crapstick.

07:44.164 --> 07:45.764
Ken: (sighs)
- it came back?

07:45.899 --> 07:47.265
- What came back?

07:47.400 --> 07:48.967
