09:25.032 --> 09:27.765
It's over.
Crystal: No! No, babe!

09:27.767 --> 09:31.136
It just means that it's time...

09:31.271 --> 09:34.339
For an upgrade.
Rhian: Seriously, ry,

09:34.408 --> 09:36.975
You're almost 40,
like, grow up.

09:37.110 --> 09:38.944
- And you had your life
all figured out?

09:39.079 --> 09:40.645
(paper thwaps)

09:40.780 --> 09:43.815
- Find an employed husband.

09:43.950 --> 09:45.416
Reproduce.

09:45.485 --> 09:48.419
Corporate and physical
moonshine domination.

09:48.488 --> 09:50.021
- She was ten.
All: (laugh)

09:50.090 --> 09:52.223
- Oh, my god, I...

09:52.225 --> 09:54.291
I should've been in charge
of the moonshine by now.

09:54.328 --> 09:56.328
Fate is mocking me!
Colin: Hey, hey!

09:56.463 --> 09:58.729
Two out of three is pretty
good. Right, guys?

09:58.765 --> 10:01.766
- Okay, let's see
what we have here.

10:01.768 --> 10:05.369
Inherit half of a bankrupt
campground. (laughs)

10:06.940 --> 10:09.474
Nora: Ah!
Completely unreadable.

10:09.609 --> 10:11.609
That can't be good.
(laughs)

10:11.612 --> 10:13.778
♪♪♪

10:13.847 --> 10:15.946
Fate is an illegible
ink blotch.

10:17.184 --> 10:20.451
- Or an opportunity to create
a bright, new future.

10:20.520 --> 10:22.420
- Is she high?
- (chuckles)

10:22.489 --> 10:24.322
- Well, I wish I had
a fresh start

10:24.324 --> 10:25.790
When I was still young enough
to enjoy it.

10:25.792 --> 10:28.193
- You're not that old.
- We're not, not that old.

10:28.328 --> 10:30.095
- (chuckles)
- argh!

10:30.097 --> 10:32.664
Maybe this is a sign.
Blank slate.

10:32.666 --> 10:34.598
The first day... Of what's left

10:34.635 --> 10:37.202
Of the rest of my life
starts right now.

10:37.337 --> 10:38.769
Whaddya say, mom, you in?
- (chuckles)

10:38.805 --> 10:40.604
(lidia's phone chimes)

10:43.810 --> 10:47.178
♪♪♪

10:47.214 --> 10:49.113
- Hmm.
- Did the universe provide?

10:50.917 --> 10:52.784
- Keep you posted, hmm.

10:54.854 --> 10:56.421
Ken: (sighs)

10:59.659 --> 11:00.959
(reads) "be free"

11:02.529 --> 11:04.162
Were we ever free?

11:04.164 --> 11:06.297
- Hard to trip the light
fantastic with five kids

11:06.433 --> 11:08.633
And a home that doubles
as a front desk.

11:08.635 --> 11:10.101
- Hmm.

11:10.137 --> 11:13.938
♪♪♪

11:13.974 --> 11:15.606
(cup clatters)

11:15.676 --> 11:18.109
(scroll rustles)

11:18.145 --> 11:19.944
- You still wanna be free,
my love?

11:19.980 --> 11:21.479
- Hells yeah.

11:21.548 --> 11:24.849
- Maybe it's time we give fate
a helping hand.

11:24.851 --> 11:28.186
♪♪♪

11:28.255 --> 11:32.523
♪♪♪

11:32.559 --> 11:35.226
- You've been staring
at that paper for hours.

11:35.262 --> 11:36.994
- With the limited life
I have remaining,

11:37.030 --> 11:38.930
It's hard to choose
just one fate, you know.

11:38.932 --> 11:40.799
- Well, it's nice that your
family has these traditions.

11:40.934 --> 11:43.201
