to celebrate.

11:51.344 --> 11:53.812
And then, run out on the bill.
- We can have traditions, too.

11:53.947 --> 11:56.814
I love pancakes!
- Ry.

11:56.883 --> 11:58.883
- With extra syrup.
- Here's the thing.

11:58.919 --> 12:03.053
Fate is just another way
of spelling "goal".

12:04.624 --> 12:06.824
You know, it's important
that you set your sights

12:06.893 --> 12:09.494
On one thing and go for it.

12:09.563 --> 12:12.030
It's-it's also um...

12:12.165 --> 12:14.565
Some might say,
easier to do sober.

12:14.634 --> 12:16.167
I'm just saying.

12:16.203 --> 12:18.068
(crystal's phone buzzes)
ooh, sorry.

12:19.706 --> 12:20.905
Oh.

12:23.310 --> 12:25.209
(phone continues to vibrate)

12:26.946 --> 12:28.480
(beeps call off)

12:28.615 --> 12:30.014
<i> Ryan: I want you to be</i>
<i> proud of me.</i>

12:31.084 --> 12:33.083
- I want me to be proud
of you, too.

12:34.254 --> 12:37.188
You and your family are um...

12:37.224 --> 12:38.990
Well, you're all I have now.

12:38.992 --> 12:41.192
So, no pressure!
(laughs)

12:44.564 --> 12:46.597
(beaded curtain jingles)

12:51.404 --> 12:53.338
- Good lord, son,

12:53.340 --> 12:55.606
Do we have to book
the plane tickets for you?

12:55.642 --> 12:57.641
Go to grad school!
Be free.

12:58.745 --> 13:00.878
Just don't send us the bill.
(laughs)

13:00.947 --> 13:03.881
- I told you I was thinking
about it. And...

13:03.950 --> 13:06.217
Where-where are you two
going?

13:06.352 --> 13:08.486
- Whichever way the wind blows.

13:08.488 --> 13:10.355
- And will the wind
