<i> A slave to a third-rate</i>
<i> campground</i>

27:47.633 --> 27:49.433
In the middle of nowhere
until I'm 70.

27:49.435 --> 27:51.635
I mean, is that my fate?
Owning 43 percent of a business

27:51.637 --> 27:53.636
That will 100 percent
destroy me?

27:53.673 --> 27:55.239
- Better you, than me.

27:55.374 --> 27:56.840
- I am not equipped to be
in charge

27:56.842 --> 27:58.509
Of my own life right now,

27:58.644 --> 28:00.243
Let alone the moonshine,
the staff,

28:00.312 --> 28:01.912
The future of this place.

28:01.914 --> 28:04.848
Just never felt so aimless.
(sighs) sex-starved.

28:06.585 --> 28:07.984
Lost!

28:08.020 --> 28:09.720
(frustrated exhale)

28:09.855 --> 28:11.755
- Are you looking to me
for advice?

28:11.824 --> 28:14.924
- You're the only one here.
- Oh! Uh... Okay.

28:14.960 --> 28:17.327
I mean, why don't you do the
thing people do with the...

28:17.329 --> 28:19.530
Closed eye and the woo-woo.

28:19.665 --> 28:21.398
- Ha, yes! Meditate.

28:21.400 --> 28:22.733
Ah, yes!

28:22.868 --> 28:24.868
The disillusion of the sense
of one's false self,

28:24.870 --> 28:27.070
In order to create
a beautiful serenity.

28:27.072 --> 28:29.339
A selfless connection
to the universe.

28:29.408 --> 28:31.207
- You know what, this would be
faster, actually.

28:31.243 --> 28:34.244
Okay, so, this is a downer.

28:34.379 --> 28:36.413
Um, or upper.

28:36.548 --> 28:38.415
Well, you'll either pass out
or clean your entire trailer.

28:38.550 --> 28:39.817
Win-win.

28:39.952 --> 28:42.986
These, okay,
with one glass of wine,

28:43.122 --> 28:45.922
Do not sext easy rider. Okay?
- Okay, okay.

28:48.093 --> 28:49.626
- (sighs)

28:49.695 --> 28:50.894
(loud gulp)

28:50.896 --> 28:54.431
Mm-hmm. This one?
Thank you.

28:54.566 --> 28:55.832
- You're welcome.

28:55.901 --> 28:57.768
♪♪♪

28:57.903 --> 29:00.037
Okay.

29:00.039 --> 29:01.772
- (gasps)

29:01.907 --> 29:03.506
(scroll flutters)

29:03.542 --> 29:05.509
Think I won't destroy you?

29:05.511 --> 29:07.076
(indistinct chatter
and laughter)

29:09.281 --> 29:11.581
<i> Lidia: "dear gale,</i>

29:11.717 --> 29:14.585
Due to unforeseen family
obligations--"

29:14.720 --> 29:16.520
(knock on door,
door creaks open)

29:16.522 --> 29:19.189
- We need to talk, mom.
- It's time.

29:19.191 --> 29:21.658
- Oh, my god, are you pregnant?
Is it drugs? Are you sick?

29:21.794 --> 29:23.660
- The only thing that's sick
is our living conditions.

29:23.729 --> 29:25.662
- We have zero privacy in here.

29:25.698 --> 29:28.599
- We need real bedrooms.
With real soundproofing.

29:28.601 --> 29:31.234
- Now that grandma and grandpa
are leaving the moonshine...

29:31.270 --> 29:33.937
- There's enough room for finn
and I in the main lodge.

29:33.973 --> 29:36.072
- You don't wanna live
with me anymore?

29:39.278 --> 29:41.011
Okay.

29:41.080 --> 29:42.479
- Really?

29:42.481 --> 29:45.616
- Go, be free.

29:45.618 --> 29:47.017
- Wow.

29:47.019 --> 29:48.685
- You've been under my wing
all summer, and...

29:48.821 --> 29:53.023
I'm cool, I get that people
need a space of their own.

29:53.025 --> 29:55.558
- Let's go before she sobers up
and changes her mind.

29:55.594 --> 29:57.961
(small laugh)
finn: Oh, okay.

29:58.096 --> 30:00.096
- Mm-hmm.
- All right.

30:00.132 --> 30:02.232
- Uh, yeah, that... That's good.

30:03.602 --> 30:05.902
<i> Nora: Goddammit!</i>

30:05.938 --> 30:08.705
Get back here, stupid thing.

30:08.741 --> 30:09.907
(gravel crunches under foot)

30:10.042 --> 30:11.875
Get back here!

30:13.779 --> 30:15.179
Damn it!

30:15.314 --> 30:17.647
(scroll rustles)

30:17.683 --> 30:21.852
♪♪♪

30:21.987 --> 30:25.589
Fine! You win!
He can stay the night!

30:26.959 --> 30:28.925
(exhales sharply)

30:29.061 --> 30:31.561
♪♪♪

30:31.563 --> 30:33.530
(water rushes)

30:35.067 --> 30:36.800
Crystal: Hmm.

30:36.802 --> 30:38.801
I'm sorry that I neglected you.

30:38.838 --> 30:40.336
(water splashes gently)

30:40.372 --> 30:42.206
Neglected myself, too.

30:46.178 --> 30:47.944
(phone buzzing)

30:50.616 --> 30:52.282
(breathes deeply)

30:52.318 --> 30:53.951
(beeps call on)

30:54.086 --> 30:56.686
<i>Operator: Collect call from hrm</i>

30:56.722 --> 30:59.089
<i> Women's correctional facility.</i>
<i> Will you accept?</i>

30:59.091 --> 31:00.958
- Yeah.

31:00.960 --> 31:02.959
Jill: Well, it's about time
you answered.

31:02.995 --> 31:05.495
- Hi, mom. Um, I'm sorry,

31:05.564 --> 31:07.197
I've just been really busy,
watering your plants.

31:07.199 --> 31:10.567
- Okay, I-I need you to load up
my commissary card.

31:10.702 --> 31:13.202
Help me figure out bail.
- Okay.

31:14.240 --> 31:16.839
I'm um...

31:16.876 --> 31:19.309
I'm really sorry about
how everything happened.

31:19.444 --> 31:21.177
<i> - You should be sorry.</i>

31:21.213 --> 31:22.913
'cause you're on your own now.

31:23.048 --> 31:25.048
- No, I'm not. I have ryan.

31:25.183 --> 31:26.983
- You think when push
comes to shove,

31:27.019 --> 31:30.487
That family is gonna go out
on a limb for ya?

31:30.489 --> 31:32.656
- So, what if they don't?

31:32.725 --> 31:35.659
I have... Myself.

31:37.363 --> 31:40.330
You know, and I am gonna
be someone, mom!

31:40.465 --> 31:42.332
I am gonna make something
of myself.

31:42.401 --> 31:44.601
That is my fate!
You will see!

31:44.736 --> 31:46.269
<i> And you know what?</i>

31:46.338 --> 31:48.338
<i> As for yours,</i>

31:48.340 --> 31:49.907
<i> In case you haven't noticed,</i>

31:50.042 --> 31:52.075
<i> You're the one in jail!</i>

31:52.111 --> 31:54.745
So, good luck getting spicy
ramen

31:54.747 --> 31:56.546
And root touch-ups on your own!

31:56.548 --> 31:58.214
(beeps call off)

32:00.085 --> 32:02.352
(phone thuds gently)

32:02.388 --> 32:03.820
(proud exhale)

32:03.956 --> 32:06.290
- Yo, gale, I'm just
gonna say it.

32:07.893 --> 32:10.727
We can't work together
because...

32:10.796 --> 32:12.896
All I wanna do is jump
your bones.

32:12.965 --> 32:15.231
(knock on door)

32:15.301 --> 32:17.367
(door creaks open)
oscar?

32:17.403 --> 32:18.802
Hey.
- Hey.

32:18.804 --> 32:20.837
Lidia, (clears throat)
I uh...

32:20.973 --> 32:23.506
I may not be a lawyer but
I could sure argue like one.

32:23.542 --> 32:25.309
- Mm-hmm.
- Rhian deserve the moonshine.

32:25.444 --> 32:27.377
She needs it. I need it,

32:27.379 --> 32:30.647
And I need you to need her
to need it, as well.

32:30.649 --> 32:33.717
- M-kay.
- What, so you'll consider it?

32:33.852 --> 32:36.352
- She didn't want it, oscar.
- (sighs)

32:36.388 --> 32:38.087
She wants it more
than anything, lidia,

32:38.123 --> 32:40.190
But she wants her family
to want her to have it.

32:40.259 --> 32:42.059
Especially you.

32:42.194 --> 32:44.327
Your approval is really
important to her.

32:44.396 --> 32:45.996
And I will deny saying that

32:46.065 --> 32:48.297
And run away if you ever
repeat those words.

32:48.334 --> 32:51.067
- Sure. Yeah.
I'll think on it.

32:51.103 --> 32:53.403
- Yes! You are a legend!
(chuckles)

32:53.538 --> 32:55.005
- Okay.

32:55.140 --> 32:57.807
- Oh um, and one more request.
- Mm-hmm.

32:57.843 --> 33:00.677
- If rhian asks, can you tell
her I put up a big fight?

33:00.746 --> 33:02.813
You know, really beat ya down.

33:02.948 --> 33:05.148
That'd be great for optics.
Big win for me, you know.

33:05.283 --> 33:07.183
- Oh, of course. Yep.

33:07.252 --> 33:09.753
- Nice. Nice. Okay, see ya!

33:09.888 --> 33:11.688
- Bye now.
- Bye! (door slams)

33:15.794 --> 33:17.360
(sighs)

33:17.429 --> 33:18.862
(flops to bed)

33:18.997 --> 33:20.430
(groans)

33:21.500 --> 33:24.234
♪♪♪

33:24.369 --> 33:26.770
I can't do your renovation.

33:28.040 --> 33:29.639
Sorry.

33:31.844 --> 33:34.344
(message sent chimes)
(coughing in back room)

33:34.479 --> 33:40.983
♪♪♪

33:41.020 --> 33:42.852
Hello?

33:45.557 --> 33:47.190
<i> (coughing continues)</i>

33:47.325 --> 33:54.263
♪♪♪

33:54.299 --> 34:00.169
♪♪♪

34:01.807 --> 34:03.440
Aunt felicia?

34:03.575 --> 34:05.809
- My least-hated niece.

34:07.913 --> 34:10.046
Missed ya, lids!
- (shocked exhale)

34:10.049 --> 34:11.214
- (chuckles)

34:14.920 --> 34:16.152
(insects buzz and chirp)

34:16.221 --> 34:20.356
♪♪♪

34:20.358 --> 34:21.958
<i> Lidia: I gave your eulogy.</i>

34:22.094 --> 34:24.961
<i> Felicia: Potato gun</i>
<i> was a nice touch.</i>

34:24.963 --> 34:26.763
- (small laugh)
- (laughs)

34:28.567 --> 34:30.900
- Is this in my head?
- Probably.

34:30.969 --> 34:32.702
- Yeah. I'll take it.

34:32.771 --> 34:34.304
(deep inhale)

34:34.306 --> 34:36.640
I need an objective ear.
(exhales)

34:36.642 --> 34:39.442
And someone to discourage me
from cutting my own bangs.

34:39.478 --> 34:41.511
- What's the problem, buddy?
- Me.

34:41.547 --> 34:44.013
My husband didn't want me.
My kids don't want me.

34:45.717 --> 34:48.385
My parents are bailing.

34:48.387 --> 34:51.387
Even the guy I wanted
to sleep with... Can't.

34:51.457 --> 34:54.524
Doesn't want me.
- Stop whining!

34:54.560 --> 34:57.393
Look around, it's a frickin'
paradise.

34:57.463 --> 35:00.130
- Sun is shining now
but the summer will end,

35:00.132 --> 35:02.398
And then what?
- (scoffs)

35:02.400 --> 35:04.967
- Why did you leave me
the moonshine?

35:05.003 --> 35:06.769
Why me?

35:10.843 --> 35:12.241
(insects chirp)

35:18.417 --> 35:20.416
- Oh, ah-ah.
Okay.

35:20.418 --> 35:23.887
- Second thoughts?
- Um... (clears throat)

35:23.956 --> 35:25.721
I don't wanna be stagnant.

35:27.426 --> 35:30.226
- Huh?
- (stammers) me and my rules,

35:30.262 --> 35:33.763
Lucky t-shirts, stupid quirks.
- No, nora, look,

35:33.799 --> 35:36.833
You don't have to change
your life for me. Okay?

35:36.835 --> 35:38.768
You need to change it for you.
If you want.

35:38.770 --> 35:40.904
- Well...
- Or not.

35:43.342 --> 35:45.441
I will love all versions of you
and I'll follow you

35:45.511 --> 35:48.110
Wherever you wanna go,
forever and ever.

35:50.649 --> 35:52.649
♪ amen
- okay, all right.

35:52.651 --> 35:54.251
Enough with the weird,
mushy shit.

35:54.386 --> 35:56.319
- Yeah.
- Okay.

35:56.321 --> 35:59.389
Okay.
Without further ado...

35:59.458 --> 36:01.057
(light switch clicks)

36:01.193 --> 36:04.194
Oh, uh, yeah.

36:04.196 --> 36:08.465
♪♪♪

36:08.600 --> 36:11.867
So, ready to do your
dirty girl?

36:12.404 --> 36:14.170
(door closes)

36:15.741 --> 36:17.773
(insects buzz)

36:21.480 --> 36:23.680
(door creaks open and slams)

36:28.220 --> 36:31.621
- I think there's uh,
a light on the porch. It's out.

36:31.756 --> 36:33.857
- Well, it's not your
responsibility, hun.

36:33.859 --> 36:36.226
- Well, maybe I should just go-

36:36.228 --> 36:39.295
- Hmm. Be free, old man.
(glasses clink)

36:39.331 --> 36:41.330
- Right.

36:42.434 --> 36:44.066
Free.

36:46.004 --> 36:49.305
(door clunks open,
ryan sings, slurring)

36:49.374 --> 36:50.974
(door shuts)

36:51.043 --> 36:52.709
- You'd think the drunk tank
would be a reason

36:52.778 --> 36:55.178
Not to finish off the rum.
Ibuprofen.

36:55.180 --> 36:57.113
For the morning,
if you make it that far.

36:57.115 --> 36:58.981
- Woo!
- Water!

36:59.017 --> 37:00.349
(rum splashes)

37:01.386 --> 37:04.320
(ryan laughs)
good as new!

37:04.389 --> 37:06.590
- As long as you don't
asphyxiate on your own vomit,

37:06.725 --> 37:08.524
And die!
- One day, little bro,

37:08.560 --> 37:10.359
I'm gonna be there
to help you out.

37:10.395 --> 37:12.395
Make all your dreams come true.

37:12.464 --> 37:14.530
We could make a new vessel
of fate!

37:14.532 --> 37:16.466
Choose your own future.

37:18.003 --> 37:20.070
- I don't know.

37:20.072 --> 37:21.605
Can we?

37:21.740 --> 37:23.539
I mean, I don't even know
where I'm from,

37:23.575 --> 37:25.375
Let alone where I'm going.

37:25.444 --> 37:28.010
- From here, silly!
From the moonshine.

37:28.046 --> 37:29.945
Right where I found ya
on that porch.

37:29.982 --> 37:33.883
Baby sammy's just so cute.
- I mean, who I'm from.

37:35.153 --> 37:36.619
You know, my biological mom.

37:37.756 --> 37:40.856
Who she is and how I wound
up here.

37:42.127 --> 37:44.427
And why she's never
come to check on me,

37:44.429 --> 37:46.997
Even though she knows
where I am.

37:48.834 --> 37:50.966
I think maybe that's why
I'm stuck.

37:52.037 --> 37:53.770
- Hmm.

37:53.772 --> 37:58.074
- Why I'm afraid of grad school
and a relationship

37:58.076 --> 38:00.043
That could take me away
from the moonshine.

38:01.113 --> 38:03.112
Part of me thinks...

38:04.182 --> 38:06.650
She could come back.

38:06.785 --> 38:08.785
- We could find her.

38:08.854 --> 38:11.620
- Mom and dad, they looked.

38:13.191 --> 38:14.624
For a really long time.

38:16.028 --> 38:18.394
- I haven't.
- You?

38:18.463 --> 38:20.530
- Fate 2.0, bro.

38:20.532 --> 38:23.099
I will make that my purpose!

38:23.101 --> 38:25.668
I will find your bio mom
for you.

38:25.671 --> 38:28.237
I'll make everyone proud.

38:28.273 --> 38:30.740
Whoa.
- Whoa, you okay?

38:33.077 --> 38:35.278
- Sammy--
- yeah?

38:35.280 --> 38:36.445
- Tuck me in?

38:39.818 --> 38:42.752
- Boundaries, remember?
- It was a test.

38:43.955 --> 38:45.821
You passed, little bro.

38:47.158 --> 38:49.559
(footsteps thud lightly,
flops to bed)

38:50.829 --> 38:53.429
(knock on door,
door creaks open)

38:58.203 --> 38:59.469
(keys jingle)

38:59.604 --> 39:01.304
- I need help.

39:01.373 --> 39:03.373
Uh...

39:03.375 --> 39:05.975
I need you take the keys,
rhian.

39:06.110 --> 39:09.913
N-no. I want you...

39:09.915 --> 39:11.981
To take the keys.

39:12.050 --> 39:19.255
♪♪♪

39:19.391 --> 39:21.490
(keys jingle)

39:25.530 --> 39:31.935
♪♪♪

39:31.937 --> 39:34.070
(footsteps recede)

39:34.072 --> 39:35.605
(footsteps crunch in the grass)

39:39.578 --> 39:43.245
(waves ripple)

39:45.917 --> 39:50.186
♪♪♪

39:50.255 --> 39:51.821
(pail clunks)

39:58.363 --> 40:00.296
(shovel scraping)

40:02.300 --> 40:04.033
(waves lap)

40:04.069 --> 40:07.536
<i>Felicia: Do you remember that</i>
<i> epic sandcastle you built</i>

40:07.572 --> 40:09.572
<i> When you were nine? Hmm?</i>

40:09.608 --> 40:11.641
<i> Spent the whole day</i>
<i> on the turrets.</i>

40:11.710 --> 40:14.844
The renegade queen's private
quarters.

40:14.846 --> 40:17.580
- (laughs) yeah, the one
with the ensuite sauna,

40:17.616 --> 40:19.849
Marble foyer.

40:19.984 --> 40:22.352
Soaker tub.
- Born architect.

40:22.487 --> 40:24.286
A true artist.

40:26.158 --> 40:28.524
Hmm. And do you remember when
that storm blew in, hmm?

40:30.261 --> 40:33.229
The tide was comin' in so fast.
Huge waves.

40:34.633 --> 40:39.469
You dragged every lawn chair
and towel down to the beach.

40:39.471 --> 40:41.004
<i> Built a barrier.</i>

40:41.006 --> 40:43.673
<i> (chuckling)</i>
<i> nine years old.</i>

40:43.742 --> 40:46.542
<i>You tried to fight the ocean.</i>

40:48.280 --> 40:50.179
<i> (laughs)</i>

40:50.182 --> 40:51.580
<i> The ocean! (laughs)</i>

40:52.684 --> 40:55.885
- I was a stupid kid.
- You were a fierce kid.

40:57.689 --> 41:00.723
A brave kid.

41:00.759 --> 41:03.459
That's why I left you
the moonshine.

41:03.462 --> 41:05.962
So that you could protect it.

41:05.964 --> 41:09.766
<i> That girl who tried</i>
<i> to fight the ocean.</i>

41:09.768 --> 41:11.968
<i> She's still in there.</i>

41:11.970 --> 41:13.569
- Is she?

41:13.704 --> 41:16.339
<i> I just feel so lost.</i>

41:17.775 --> 41:21.110
<i> Felicia: You know, you can't</i>
<i> put fate in a bottle, hmm.</i>

41:21.179 --> 41:22.044
<i> Wish ya could.</i>

41:23.114 --> 41:27.183
♪♪♪

41:27.318 --> 41:29.652
(yells) just try me!
(waves crash)

41:29.654 --> 41:32.322
I dare you, bring it, bitch!

41:32.324 --> 41:34.423
I don't need your permission!

41:34.459 --> 41:36.792
Or some stupid fate scroll!

41:38.396 --> 41:39.762
I got this!

41:42.066 --> 41:44.367
<i> Felicia: Life will show up</i>

41:44.502 --> 41:46.469
<i> When you least expect it.</i>

41:46.471 --> 41:47.704
(waves crash)

41:47.706 --> 41:50.139
And the lidia that I know
can handle

41:50.141 --> 41:52.708
Anything that it throws
her way.

41:55.413 --> 41:57.280
- I'm not ready.

41:58.984 --> 42:01.150
I'm not ready.

42:01.186 --> 42:06.890
♪♪♪

42:09.360 --> 42:11.160
(glass scrapes)

42:11.229 --> 42:14.530
(roxy: "take a chance with me")

42:14.566 --> 42:17.500
(approaching motorcycle engine
rumbles)

42:17.569 --> 42:22.105
♪♪♪

42:22.107 --> 42:24.006
(engine rumbles)

42:25.443 --> 42:27.043
(engine stops)

42:29.214 --> 42:37.153
♪♪♪

42:37.222 --> 42:43.392
♪♪♪

42:43.428 --> 42:44.994
- I lied.

42:46.998 --> 42:49.265
Renovation,
that was a euphemism.

42:49.267 --> 42:57.273
♪♪♪

42:57.408 --> 43:00.042
♪ I was lost,
can't ya see ♪

43:01.479 --> 43:05.280
♪♪♪

43:05.317 --> 43:08.618
♪ through the long
lonely night ♪

43:08.620 --> 43:10.252
Lidia: Woo!

43:10.322 --> 43:13.689
♪♪♪

43:19.898 --> 43:26.836
♪♪♪

43:26.905 --> 43:33.843
♪♪♪

43:33.912 --> 43:39.916
♪♪♪

43:39.918 --> 43:46.088
♪♪♪
